caption: I got their panaeng curry and it was the most disappointing panaeng I've ever had. The curry consistency was watery and it just had chicken and broccoli in it, nothing else... I usually am able to make my curry into 2 meals at any other thai place but I ate everything in one sitting... save yourself the disappointment and go to Sage just a few blocks away. Quality and quantity is poor here.
Good food, and services. Recommended.

Have ordered delivery from Thip Osha ~100 times over the last two years and have been there physically a few times too; timely and absolutely delicious every time. Thank you for the incredible service and food!
food is delicious and well made!!! Highly recommended

My official neighborhood spot! Everything I’ve gotten has been delicious and bursting with flavor. Go-to favorites are the shredded papaya salad and the chive pancakes. The Thai iced tea is perfectly made and the soups have all been spot-on. Thanks for making COVID times a little easier and more delicious.

Thip Osha is a neighborhood gem. There's a couple of options for Thai in the area, including Sage just a few blocks away, but I've found Thip Osha to be more consistent for takeout. They fulfill pickup orders extremely fast-- I'm talking like 10 minutes, piping hot and tasty. I noticed prices went up a bit for protein options in their dishes unfortunately so I usually go with vegetables which I've actually come to like more anyway. Their Spicy Basil Fried Rice is my go-to.
Great food for the price, very tasty. I would have given 5 Stars but they removed Desserts off the online menu, which is one of the main reasons I liked this place. Bring the desserts back!!
Thip osha should have ka boom keen bam ya poo in Grubhub options so that is why I don’t need to call the restaurant every single time.

The worst Thai food I've ever tasted.The Shrimp thai rice was clumpy and soggy.Probably old and the slice of lime that they put next to the salad was dried and old and stringy and no juice came out when I squeezed it
All dishes were excellent! Green curry with salmon was very tasty. Take out available. Very clean.
Amazing! Can’t believe this gem hidden in Williamsburg

This place is AMAZING!! I've had their Pad Thai before, and I recently tried their Udon Curry Soup, Mango Sticky rice, and Thai tea!! Can I just say it was so delicious and full of flavor.  The people who work there are also so kind and welcoming!! I totally recommend this place to anyone and everyone 😁👍

Thip Osha is our favorite restaurant in the neighborhood! We've eaten here for two years and never been disappointed. Their red curry is rich and spicy. The cocunut custards (when available) are the stuff of dessert dreams.
The food is really awesome and comes in good sizes. They also deliver pretty fast.

Thip Osha is like a friend who always has your back. I’ve ordered from this place 5+ times and it never fails to disappoint. The duck curry is spicy and rich and has SO much crispy-skinned, juicy duck. My roommate got the tom yum seafood noodle soup and it was delicious as well— plus they were accommodating of all her substitution requests! I will be very sad if I ever move out of their delivery range <3
Fantastic food.  Great price. Hidden gem in East Williamsburg
Dank duck noodle soup. Dumplings were awesome. Enjoyed my meal very much
The most auth budget thai in nyc
Omg!!!!!! Great THAI FOOD.
Best Thai food I've ever had in New York. By far.
I go for the lunch specials, which are very good and plentiful. A bargain. Nice people too.
Affordable lunch special: Ordered Chicken Pangyang with Fritters, excellent! Lots of Chicken in the Curry. Submerge your rice in curry, it seems a little thin but works perfect.
Very filling lunch special on a budget. Super nice people.
Good tests.
Great thai food! Very spicey and authentic!

I came here for lunch on a weekend again for the lunch special, and I again got the pad kee mao with tofu and dumplings as the appetizer. I ate in the restaurant this time though, and it was equally tasty! I do want to note that the tofu is firm tofu and not fried tofu, and the tofu flavor's not great. There's also not very many vegetables in the pad kee mao, which is a bit disappointing. The noodles themselves are chewy and delicious, and the flavor is bold. It's also sufficiently spicy! Amount of food is good for the lunch special price of $9.50 pre-tax pre-tip, as it comes with a salad, a (small) appetizer, and the main dish.

We order from here all the time and it’s easily the best Thai food in the neighborhood. It’s consistently delicious and freshly prepared. The dishes have heaps of vegetables and garnished with herbs - a rarity with other places. Delivery and pickup is always super quick. The lunch specials are great value. Requests are always accommodated. Nothing bad to say - it’s a gem.
Great price for big portions. Get Tom kha soup, very good.
A step above other Thai places. The best of many in the hood.
Loved the portions/prices. Yellow curry and steamed veggies were delicious, and they delivered fast. No complaints here
They soo rude. keep asking tip from me.
Some of the best Thai food I've had in the city.
(Translated by Google) Yummmmmm  (Original) Yummmmmm
Great food, fast delivery service and very flexible with requests!! Love it
Most disgusting food Ive ever had in my life. No type of seasoning, no flavor whatsoever
Absolutely delicious food, great service, wonderful gastronomic experience!!
Food is fresh and portions are very generous as well as good service. Would recommend to people in the area.

So tasty! Ordered the beef pad Thai and it is the best I’ve had in the neighborhood, very saucy with large meaty chunks of beef. Yum! Meant to eat half and save half for the next day but ate the full order.
(Translated by Google) Delicious tai food in ny  (Original) Deliciosa comida tai en ny
Authentic Thai,take it from me I've actually been to Thailand.I highly recommend the Kao chow soup .Best soup you've had in a while.

Happened to stuble apon this place one day while walking around so we gave it a shot. It definitely was a good choice. The food was very reasonable priced. We ordered an appetizer which was the papya salad and a soup to share since it was kind of a chilly day out. Both were very delicious and one of the best papya salads I had in Brooklyn. The soup was also very good. The broth was full of flavor as well it was the one with the duck. It's definitely big enough for two to share. The staff was very friendly and helped accommodate us. Would definitely recommend this place if you are in the area.

This is the most dishonest restaurant ever. They charged me an 18% tips using after tax amount in the receipt already. And then the waitress hided the receipt with the price breakdown and gave me another credit card receipt, expecting me to give an extra 18% tips. It is totally unacceptable. And the waitress didn't even feel sorry for her unethical act at all after I pointed it out.
Great place! Delicious food & super accommodating staff.

This is the rudest, most unprofessional restaurant I've ever encountered. I used to eat here when it was another Thai  restaurant so I was curious about it. The restaurant was almost empty when the three of us walked in. All the tables are 2-seaters. "Can we move another chair to a table?" we asked.  "No," they said.  We stared at them and each other. Yes, they couldn't do anything for us. We left.  I went back twice more. Once at 3:30, and once at 3:50. (The alleged "lunch special" goes until 4.) Both times they were sitting inside and the closed sign was on the door. The second time I pushed it open and they confirmed that they were closed.  I dunno, I guess they just got tired of cooking and figured they'd have a cigarette or watch TV or something.  On the plus side, it's nice they're not overly burdened with responsibility. It's nice they listen to their inner voices. On the minus side, it's too bad their inner voices say "F*** all these damn people who want food!" They need to get into a business where their attitude would be appreciated. Maybe as IRS accountants, or spokespeople for President Trump.
Panang curry like woah

Great place with great food. I love Moo Ping (Thai grilled marinated pork) eat with sticky rice and beef salad. So tasty yum. This place is one of the best Thai food and by the way forgot to mentioned that I’m Thai:).
My go-to place for quick takeout. I love the spicy basil fried rice. Prices are great too.
Delicious food for a great price. Highly recommend.

The food is awesome the staff is friendly great customer service overall I came here like 3 times with my mother and it was amazing the food and the decorations to also it was a very enjoyable experience and I would definitely recommend this place to anyone

So far so good. I ordered  Chicken Pad see Ew and Tom Yum for Delivery and it came on time and hot. I have been looking for good Thai Delivery to Bushwick, and I think I found it! Next I have to try the Chicken Pad thai and Golden fritter. Until then I will see how I feel about this place.

You won't find a lot of bells and whistles with the food here -- simplicity is the goal and it works out just fine. The food is delicious, always brought out hot and fresh. For the price, this place is an absolute steal. I highly recommend the pad see ew.
Amazing!
Really delicious 😋
Last night i order the chu chee salmon and panang curry. The food was so good and even take out presentation like dine in. Great!! Service

The food was tasty and the service was excellent. We ordered the Tom yum, Som Tum, curry puffs, and pad krapow. Everything was deliciously authentic, but the Som tum was definitely the highlight. My roommate and I are both Thai and really glad this place opened up right across the street from our apt. It's not as good as some of the Thai food in queens, but probably one of the best places I've tried in Brooklyn.
Terrific authentic thai food, would recommend take out before dining in though. Place is a tad bit small.

Stopped in after work to sit and eat. Asked to wash my hands and waitress said ' we don't have a place to wash hands'. Are you freaking kidding me! Food sub par..service sucks. I was served water in a blue plastic kiddie cup!
Love them, best thai ever,

I won't ever eat here again, ever Small sitting area Place have a bad musky order Furniture needs updating, plus the place is not welcoming, just terrible...smdh. Food make cheaply and greasy, distasteful It's a run down shack place I wouldn't recommend this place to Noone, Ever Poor service and presentation Lack of cleanliness + atmosphere is very poor- it's like an outhouse dirty kitchen. Just a distasteful place to even consider going....Better elsewhere, with better quality.
Order Gai gob grob it's the best!
Best Thai in the neighborhood. Fast, clean, no fuss. Hope they never change.
Great food! My pad Thai was yummy but keep in mind there is no bathroom and they only take cash.

I hate giving negative reviews but this place was terrible. We ordered our food over the phone and had to wait for an hour and a half. We called after half hour and they just blew us off and said it was on the way. We finally got the food and the portions were just so small. Food was generic and service was poor.
Thai food by Thai people.  One of the best Thai spots in NYC.  Their fried rice is perfectly executed.

Color me shocked: this is the best Thai in the neighborhood, and that's including Pagoda, Sage, Lily Thai, and Cheers. I highly recommend the lunch special, with an entree & rice, a spring roll, and a salad clocking in at less than $7.  I toss out the standard-issue spring roll that'd get a gold medal in wonton-skin crunchiness but fails to qualify with either filling or taste, and the salad is small and dull. The entrees, though, are exemplary. The curries are beautifully seasoned and fresh-tasting, and the basil chicken is a favorite. Sure, they're a little short on chicken, but did you miss the part where I said they're UNDER SEVEN BUCKS?

We had dinner here. The duck curry was great! The duck was cook good for a curry and it had just enough kick.  Ba mee was a little bland bit was still good. This place is definitely worth checking out. I'm sure we'll be back if we are in the area
